_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

instructionForBlock: This is a practice block. For each trial of this experiment, you are first tracking a white moving crosshair with your cursor. The white crosshair is surrounded by three yellow crosshairs that are also moving. Regardless, keep tracking the WHITE crosshair with your cursor: keep both the cursor and your gaze AT THE CENTER of the white crosshair. The crosshair is *bolded* when you are successfully tracking. After tracking the crosshair for a while, a pair of vertical lines will flash on either the left or the right of the crosshair. The two lines are stacked, with an offset. Your job is to decide whether the TOP line is shifted to the Left or to the Right, relative to the lower line. Respond by clicking the “Left” or the “Right” buttons at the end of the trial. If you answer correctly, you will hear a “Beep”. When the lines flash, it will be tempting to move your gaze and look for them. However, PLEASE KEEP YOUR GAZE ON THE CROSSHAIR! View the letters with your side vision.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForBlock: This is a practice block. For each trial of this experiment, you are first tracking a white moving crosshair with your cursor. The white crosshair is surrounded by three yellow crosshairs that are also moving. Regardless, keep tracking the WHITE crosshair with your cursor: keep both the cursor and your gaze AT THE CENTER of the white crosshair. The crosshair is *bolded* when you are successfully tracking. After tracking the crosshair for a while, a pair of vertical lines will flash on either the left or the right of the crosshair. The two lines are stacked, with an offset. Your job is to decide whether the TOP line is shifted to the Left or to the Right, relative to the lower line. Respond by clicking the “Left” or the “Right” buttons at the end of the trial. If you answer correctly, you will hear a “Beep”. When the lines flash, it will be tempting to move your gaze and look for them. However, PLEASE KEEP YOUR GAZE ON THE CROSSHAIR! View the letters with your side vision.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_calibrateMicrophoneKeywords: UMIK-1, UMIK-2, Bluetooth, Headset, Headphones, Wireless, On-Ear, Over-Ear, In-Ear, Buds, Earbuds, AirPods, Eardrops, Air, Cloud, MIDI, Line-in, Audeze, Audio-Technica, Blackwire, Beats, beyerdynamic, Blue Satellite, BlueParrot, Bowers & Wilkins, Caymuller, Bose, Conambo, COOSII, Cowin, Discover, Focal, HD, HEIBAS, HIFIMAN, HyperX, Jabra, JBL, Koss, LEVN, Logitech, Meze, Monolith, NANAMI, Poly Voyager, Porta, Raycon, Sennheiser, Shure, Sony, Soundcore, TOZO, Trucker, Vibe, Yealink
_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForBlock: Here comes the full experiment. The trials are exactly the same as what you’ve seen in the practice. Track the WHITE crosshair with your cursor. Keep both the cursor and your gaze AT THE CENTER of the crosshair. After the two vertical lines flash, report whether the TOP line is shifted to the left or to the right. If you answer correctly, you will hear a “Beep”. Again, PLEASE KEEP YOUR GAZE ON THE CROSSHAIR! View the lines with your side vision.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_calibrateMicrophoneKeywords: UMIK-1, UMIK-2, Bluetooth, Headset, Headphones, Wireless, On-Ear, Over-Ear, In-Ear, Buds, Earbuds, AirPods, Eardrops, Air, Cloud, MIDI, Line-in, Audeze, Audio-Technica, Blackwire, Beats, beyerdynamic, Blue Satellite, BlueParrot, Bowers & Wilkins, Caymuller, Bose, Conambo, COOSII, Cowin, Discover, Focal, HD, HEIBAS, HIFIMAN, HyperX, Jabra, JBL, Koss, LEVN, Logitech, Meze, Monolith, NANAMI, Poly Voyager, Porta, Raycon, Sennheiser, Shure, Sony, Soundcore, TOZO, Trucker, Vibe, Yealink
_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForBlock: Here comes the full experiment. The trials are exactly the same as what you’ve seen in the practice. Track the WHITE crosshair with your cursor. Keep both the cursor and your gaze AT THE CENTER of the crosshair. After the two vertical lines flash, report whether the TOP line is shifted to the left or to the right. If you answer correctly, you will hear a “Beep”. Again, PLEASE KEEP YOUR GAZE ON THE CROSSHAIR! View the lines with your side vision.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.

instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_calibrateMicrophoneKeywords: UMIK-1, UMIK-2, Bluetooth, Headset, Headphones, Wireless, On-Ear, Over-Ear, In-Ear, Buds, Earbuds, AirPods, Eardrops, Air, Cloud, MIDI, Line-in, Audeze, Audio-Technica, Blackwire, Beats, beyerdynamic, Blue Satellite, BlueParrot, Bowers & Wilkins, Caymuller, Bose, Conambo, COOSII, Cowin, Discover, Focal, HD, HEIBAS, HIFIMAN, HyperX, Jabra, JBL, Koss, LEVN, Logitech, Meze, Monolith, NANAMI, Poly Voyager, Porta, Raycon, Sennheiser, Shure, Sony, Soundcore, TOZO, Trucker, Vibe, Yealink
_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForBlock: You are about to begin the next block. The trials are exactly the same as what you’ve seen in the practice. Track the WHITE crosshair with your cursor. Keep both the cursor and your gaze AT THE CENTER of the crosshair. After the two vertical lines flash, report whether the TOP line is shifted to the left or to the right. If you answer correctly, you will hear a “Beep”. Again, PLEASE KEEP YOUR GAZE ON THE CROSSHAIR! View the lines with your side vision.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_calibrateMicrophoneKeywords: UMIK-1, UMIK-2, Bluetooth, Headset, Headphones, Wireless, On-Ear, Over-Ear, In-Ear, Buds, Earbuds, AirPods, Eardrops, Air, Cloud, MIDI, Line-in, Audeze, Audio-Technica, Blackwire, Beats, beyerdynamic, Blue Satellite, BlueParrot, Bowers & Wilkins, Caymuller, Bose, Conambo, COOSII, Cowin, Discover, Focal, HD, HEIBAS, HIFIMAN, HyperX, Jabra, JBL, Koss, LEVN, Logitech, Meze, Monolith, NANAMI, Poly Voyager, Porta, Raycon, Sennheiser, Shure, Sony, Soundcore, TOZO, Trucker, Vibe, Yealink
_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_calibrateMicrophoneKeywords: UMIK-1, UMIK-2, Bluetooth, Headset, Headphones, Wireless, On-Ear, Over-Ear, In-Ear, Buds, Earbuds, AirPods, Eardrops, Air, Cloud, MIDI, Line-in, Audeze, Audio-Technica, Blackwire, Beats, beyerdynamic, Blue Satellite, BlueParrot, Bowers & Wilkins, Caymuller, Bose, Conambo, COOSII, Cowin, Discover, Focal, HD, HEIBAS, HIFIMAN, HyperX, Jabra, JBL, Koss, LEVN, Logitech, Meze, Monolith, NANAMI, Poly Voyager, Porta, Raycon, Sennheiser, Shure, Sony, Soundcore, TOZO, Trucker, Vibe, Yealink
_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_calibrateMicrophoneKeywords: UMIK-1, UMIK-2, Bluetooth, Headset, Headphones, Wireless, On-Ear, Over-Ear, In-Ear, Buds, Earbuds, AirPods, Eardrops, Air, Cloud, MIDI, Line-in, Audeze, Audio-Technica, Blackwire, Beats, beyerdynamic, Blue Satellite, BlueParrot, Bowers & Wilkins, Caymuller, Bose, Conambo, COOSII, Cowin, Discover, Focal, HD, HEIBAS, HIFIMAN, HyperX, Jabra, JBL, Koss, LEVN, Logitech, Meze, Monolith, NANAMI, Poly Voyager, Porta, Raycon, Sennheiser, Shure, Sony, Soundcore, TOZO, Trucker, Vibe, Yealink
_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_calibrateMicrophoneKeywords: UMIK-1, UMIK-2, Bluetooth, Headset, Headphones, Wireless, On-Ear, Over-Ear, In-Ear, Buds, Earbuds, AirPods, Eardrops, Air, Cloud, MIDI, Line-in, Audeze, Audio-Technica, Blackwire, Beats, beyerdynamic, Blue Satellite, BlueParrot, Bowers & Wilkins, Caymuller, Bose, Conambo, COOSII, Cowin, Discover, Focal, HD, HEIBAS, HIFIMAN, HyperX, Jabra, JBL, Koss, LEVN, Logitech, Meze, Monolith, NANAMI, Poly Voyager, Porta, Raycon, Sennheiser, Shure, Sony, Soundcore, TOZO, Trucker, Vibe, Yealink
_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForBlock: You are about to begin the next block. The trials are exactly the same as what you’ve seen in the practice. Track the WHITE crosshair with your cursor. Keep both the cursor and your gaze AT THE CENTER of the crosshair. After the two vertical lines flash, report whether the TOP line is shifted to the left or to the right. If you answer correctly, you will hear a “Beep”. Again, PLEASE KEEP YOUR GAZE ON THE CROSSHAIR! View the lines with your side vision.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_calibrateMicrophoneKeywords: UMIK-1, UMIK-2, Bluetooth, Headset, Headphones, Wireless, On-Ear, Over-Ear, In-Ear, Buds, Earbuds, AirPods, Eardrops, Air, Cloud, MIDI, Line-in, Audeze, Audio-Technica, Blackwire, Beats, beyerdynamic, Blue Satellite, BlueParrot, Bowers & Wilkins, Caymuller, Bose, Conambo, COOSII, Cowin, Discover, Focal, HD, HEIBAS, HIFIMAN, HyperX, Jabra, JBL, Koss, LEVN, Logitech, Meze, Monolith, NANAMI, Poly Voyager, Porta, Raycon, Sennheiser, Shure, Sony, Soundcore, TOZO, Trucker, Vibe, Yealink
_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForBlock: You are about to begin the next block. The trials are exactly the same as what you’ve seen in the practice. Track the WHITE crosshair with your cursor. Keep both the cursor and your gaze AT THE CENTER of the crosshair. After the two vertical lines flash, report whether the TOP line is shifted to the left or to the right. If you answer correctly, you will hear a “Beep”. Again, PLEASE KEEP YOUR GAZE ON THE CROSSHAIR! View the lines with your side vision.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForBlock: You are about to begin the next block. The trials are exactly the same as what you’ve seen in the practice. Track the WHITE crosshair with your cursor. Keep both the cursor and your gaze AT THE CENTER of the crosshair. After the two vertical lines flash, report whether the TOP line is shifted to the left or to the right. If you answer correctly, you will hear a “Beep”. Again, PLEASE KEEP YOUR GAZE ON THE CROSSHAIR! View the lines with your side vision.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_calibrateMicrophoneKeywords: UMIK-1, UMIK-2, Bluetooth, Headset, Headphones, Wireless, On-Ear, Over-Ear, In-Ear, Buds, Earbuds, AirPods, Eardrops, Air, Cloud, MIDI, Line-in, Audeze, Audio-Technica, Blackwire, Beats, beyerdynamic, Blue Satellite, BlueParrot, Bowers & Wilkins, Caymuller, Bose, Conambo, COOSII, Cowin, Discover, Focal, HD, HEIBAS, HIFIMAN, HyperX, Jabra, JBL, Koss, LEVN, Logitech, Meze, Monolith, NANAMI, Poly Voyager, Porta, Raycon, Sennheiser, Shure, Sony, Soundcore, TOZO, Trucker, Vibe, Yealink
_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForBlock: You are about to begin the next block. The trials are exactly the same as what you’ve seen in the practice. Track the WHITE crosshair with your cursor. Keep both the cursor and your gaze AT THE CENTER of the crosshair. After the two vertical lines flash, report whether the TOP line is shifted to the left or to the right. If you answer correctly, you will hear a “Beep”. Again, PLEASE KEEP YOUR GAZE ON THE CROSSHAIR! View the lines with your side vision.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.

_online2Description: WARNING: To participate you must have a computer with at least 6 CPU cores, be using Chrome or Edge web browsers, and must have a functioning webcam. Otherwise, the experiment won't work and your submission will be rejected.  In this experiment, you will complete a series of reading tasks. You will be asked to rate and answer questions about different passages and you will perform letter identification tasks. Some of the tasks may be hard, so just try your best. No photos or video are recorded. Each webcam frame is used only inside your computer, solely to estimate where your eyes are and where they are looking, and then erased, within 10 seconds. Only the eye and gaze positions are retained.
instructionForStimulus: Ready? Track the white crosshair with your cursor to initiate the trial. Keep your eyes on the crosshair.
